openbroadcaster (4.4.0) focal; urgency=low

  * Production-Ready Release
  * Fixed microphone state persistence across application restart
  * Automatic microphone device fallback to first available device
  * Added Bottom-of-Hour (BOH) automation feature for 30-minute injection cycles
  * BOH enable checkbox now in Automation tab for easy access
  * Removed Master Volume control from Audio settings tab (controlled only by program level slider)
  * Cleaned up Audio tab to show only device selectors (Main Output, Mic Input)
  * Avalonia cross-platform UI layer with identical behavior on Windows and Linux
  * PulseAudio primary audio backend with ALSA and JACK fallback support
  * Complete device resolution and enumeration for Linux audio systems
  * All 86 unit tests passing
  * BuildAssembly and run identical source code on Windows and Linux

